levelledPara.title: Aspirator
levelledPara.para: The aspirator (ASP-372B) consists of a nozzle and a diffuser pressed into a standard tee fitting. The aspirator is located on the left-hand side at the front of the baseplate in the operator's position behind the degasser drain valve module. The inlet of the aspirator is piped to the discharge side of the blower in the recycle loop system. The suction side is connected to the blower motor housing drain. The discharge is connected to the collector. The purpose of the aspirator is to keep liquid from collecting in the blower motor assembly.
